From: Jack Xiao <Jack.Xiao@amd.com>
Date: Fri, 21 Apr 2023 14:20:38 +0800
Subject: drm/amdgpu: fix memory leak in mes self test
Git-commit: 31d7c3a4fc3d312a0646990767647925d5bde540
Patch-mainline: v6.5-rc1
References: jsc#PED-3527 jsc#PED-5475 jsc#PED-6068 jsc#PED-6070 jsc#PED-6116 jsc#PED-6120 jsc#PED-5065 jsc#PED-5477 jsc#PED-5511 jsc#PED-6041 jsc#PED-6069 jsc#PED-6071

The fences associated with mes queue have to be freed
up during amdgpu_ring_fini.

Signed-off-by: Jack Xiao <Jack.Xiao@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Hawking Zhang <Hawking.Zhang@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Acked-by: Patrik Jakobsson <pjakobsson@suse.de>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_ring.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_ring.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_ring.c
index 2fc498220234..54ea0a0aaa8c 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_ring.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_ring.c
@@ -390,6 +390,8 @@ void amdgpu_ring_fini(struct amdgpu_ring *ring)
 		amdgpu_bo_free_kernel(&ring->ring_obj,
 				      &ring->gpu_addr,
 				      (void **)&ring->ring);
+	} else {
+		kfree(ring->fence_drv.fences);
 	}
 
 	dma_fence_put(ring->vmid_wait);
